  "prompt": "How many books does an average person read in a year?",
  "response": "The average number of books read by a person in a year can vary significantly based on factors such as age, education level, cultural background, and personal interests. According to surveys in the United States, recent data suggests that adults typically read about 12 books per year on average, but the median number is closer to 4 books per year, indicating that a smaller number of people read a large number of books while most read fewer. Globally, the figures can differ, with some countries reporting higher averages and others lower. Ultimately, reading habits can be highly individual.",
